1032.question: Do sluice networks outperform non-transfer learning approaches?

7-Table3-1.png: Yes, the sluice networks outperform non-transfer learning approaches. The table shows that sluice networks achieve higher accuracy scores on both in-domain and out-of-domain test sets compared to baselines. Additionally, they reduce errors by an average of 12.8% for in-domain tasks and 8.9% for out-of-domain tasks.
